                  "REAC"
                ],
                "institute": "1USAWSU"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment performed at 1 MW TRIGA",
                "thermal research reactor at Washington State University"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Gamma spectra of fission products were",
                "detected using HpGE detectors"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "CHSEP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Activation method was used"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The thermal sample was irradiated for 322 s in reactor",
                "position E9, outside the reactor core. The non-thermal",
                "sample was irradiated for 200 min in position D8(closer",
                "to the core than E9) for exposure to the highest",
                "neutron flux. The non-thermal sample was irradiated in",
                "a natural boron carbide (B4C) capsule, snugly wrapped",
                "in cadmium sheeting (0.020 in. thick) with 1/2 in.",
                "overlap in the circumference.",
                "Two sets of high purity metal wires were used to",
                "characterize neutron fluence and spectrum for each",
                "uranium sample. The experimental measurements and the",
                "mcnp model were used as input into the STAYSL PNNL code",
                "that provided an experimentally adjusted neutron",
                "spectra."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The B4C neutron spectrum was a little harder than A",
                "fast flux reactor, but a bit softer than the COMET",
                "experiment and 235U fission neutron spectrum.",
                "The thermal spectrum of WSU E9 and B4C capsule spectrum",
                "is presented in fig.2 in Rad.Nucl.Chem.,296,763,2013."
              ]
            }
          ],
